author: COMSOL
description: This tutorial model presents a study of a negative corona discharge in dry air at atmospheric pressure in a point-to-plane configuration. A millimeter-sized elliptical electrode creates a high-intensity electric field where the corona discharge occurs. A ground plane is placed 10 cm away from the corona electrode. The voltage is varied between -5 and -50 kV. The creation and transport of charged species is solved self-consistently coupled with Poisson’s equation. The local field approximation is used, which means that transport and source coefficients are assumed to be well parameterized through the reduced electric field.
